         <div xml:id="alalal-h80613"><!-- l4d20a10 -->
            <head xml:id="alalal-h80613-Hd1e99">Articulus 10</head>
            <head xml:id="alalal-h80613-Hd1e101" type="question-title">An veniale peccatum potest mutari in
mortale peccatum ?</head>
            <p xml:id="alalal-h80613-d1e104">
               <pb ed="#Be" n="842"/>
               <cb ed="#Be" n="a"/>
               <lb ed="#Be" n="1"/>ARTICULUS X.
<lb ed="#Be" n="2"/>An veniale peccatum potest mutari in
<lb ed="#Be" n="3"/>mortale peccatum ?
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-h80613-d1e117">
               <lb ed="#Be" n="4"/>Deinde queritur de hoc quod dicit,
<lb ed="#Be" n="5"/>ibi, B, sub finem: <quote xml:id="alalal-h80613-Qd1e123"> Quaedam enim 
pec<lb break="no" ed="#Be" n="6"/>cata mortalia, etc. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-h80613-d1e129">
               <lb ed="#Be" n="7"/>Contra :
<lb ed="#Be" n="8"/>Sciunt artifices alchimie species 
trans<lb break="no" ed="#Be" n="9"/>mutari non posse : sed diverse sunt 
spe<lb break="no" ed="#Be" n="10"/>cies peccati, veniale et mortale: ergo
<lb ed="#Be" n="11"/>unum non transmutatur in aliud.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-h80613-d1e143">
               <lb ed="#Be" n="12"/>Sotvtio. Dicendum, quod veniale ex
<lb ed="#Be" n="13"/>genere, numquam fit mortale nisi per
<lb ed="#Be" n="14"/>modum supra dictum *: nec mortale fit
<lb ed="#Be" n="15"/>hoc modo veniale,sed mortale fit veniale
<lb ed="#Be" n="16"/>ex eventu, id est venia in poena 
expia<lb break="no" ed="#Be" n="17"/>bile, eo quod Deus delet culpam per
<lb ed="#Be" n="18"/>suam gratiam, quae facit postea 
solubi<lb break="no" ed="#Be" n="19"/>lem reatum.
</p>
         </div>
